<h1>Banana Coconut Ice Cream</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>4 ripe bananas, peeled, frozen</li>
<li>1 14-oz can coconut milk</li>
<li>2 tablespoons maple syrup</li>
<li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
<li>A pinch of salt</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Freeze the Bananas:</strong><br />
   Place the sliced bananas in a single layer on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Freeze them for at least 2-3 hours or overnight until solid# Vegan Banana Coconut Ice Cream</li>
</ol>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>4 ripe bananas, peeled and sliced</li>
<li>1/2 cup coconut milk</li>
<li>2 tbsp maple syrup</li>
<li>1 tsp vanilla extract</li>
<li>A pinch of salt</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
<li>Blend all ingredients together in a blender.</li>
<li>Serve immediately or freeze before serving.</li>
</ol>
